<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1929,2032]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1440,152,487]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
This small section with c. 3 species was described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[772,1023,1929,1955]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[880,938,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
to encompass those species having a branched inflorescence with alternate phyllotaxis (for a detailed morphological character data, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[151,210,2007,2032]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). The only member of this section included in analyses of nrITS and plastid sequences in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[151,210,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1879" box="[311,503,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dschungarica">
<emphasis box="[311,503,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. dschungarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is sister to species of 
<emphasis box="[770,795,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[863,975,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
in our studies. It was placed in 
<emphasis box="[1350,1376,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[151,304,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Monophyllos</emphasis>
Pascher subsection 
<emphasis box="[540,644,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Minimae</emphasis>
Pascher by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stroh, G." box="[787,938,190,216]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="485 - 520" refId="ref10868" refString="Stroh, G. (1937) Die Gattung Gagea Salisb. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 57: 485 - 520." type="journal article" year="1937">Stroh (1937)</bibRefCitation>
, which is also sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Royle" box="[1210,1402,191,216]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunawurensis">
<emphasis box="[1210,1402,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. kunawurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<emphasis box="[151,176,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[247,361,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
) in analyses conducted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[693,928,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[774,835,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. Pedicel anatomy (
<typeStatus box="[1157,1210,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
II) is shared by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1879" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dschungarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. dschungarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Royle" box="[366,558,268,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunawurensis">
<emphasis box="[366,558,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. kunawurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, basal leaf anatomy (
<typeStatus box="[926,978,268,294]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
II) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1879" box="[1050,1240,268,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dschungarica">
<emphasis box="[1050,1240,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. dschungarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[185,279,306,331]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis box="[185,279,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. lutea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Terracciano" authorityYear="1904" box="[348,476,306,331]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis box="[348,476,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1879" box="[493,746,306,331]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dschungarica">
<emphasis box="[493,746,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea dschungarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been grouped with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grossheim" authorityYear="1935" box="[1040,1230,306,331]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caroli-kochii">
<emphasis box="[1040,1230,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. caroli-kochii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[1291,1436,306,331]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bulbifera">
<emphasis box="[1291,1436,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. bulbifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its microreticulate pollen 
<typeStatus box="[649,704,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." box="[725,1005,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre 2005</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1879" box="[1166,1381,345,370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dschungarica">
<emphasis box="[1166,1381,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. dschungarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has morphological characters distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Royle" box="[610,802,384,409]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunawurensis">
<emphasis box="[610,802,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. kunawurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related taxa. Thus, establishment of a new section is not appropriate, and it should be placed in a more broadly defined section that includes all members in clade D in Figure 4 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[347,574,461,487]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[426,484,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
